# Bandit Level 7

## Goal
Find the password stored in data.txt next to the word "millionth".
The file has millions of lines — reading it manually is impossible.

## What I learned
- How to use grep to find one specific line in a massive file
- How to combine cat and grep using the pipe | operator

## My Approach

```bash
# Used cat to read the file and piped it into grep
# to find the line containing the word "millionth"
cat data.txt | grep "millionth"

# grep instantly returned the one line with the password
```

## Breaking down the command

```
cat data.txt    ← read the entire file
|               ← pipe — feed output into next command
grep "millionth"← find only lines containing this word
```

## Why this works
The file has millions of lines but grep scans through all of them
in milliseconds and returns only the matching line.
Without grep you would have to read millions of lines manually.

## Key commands learned
| Command | What it does |
|---------|-------------|
| `grep "word" file` | Find lines containing word |
| `cat file | grep "word"` | Pipe cat output into grep |
| `|` | Pipe — connects two commands together |

